title: Literature and the Arts (gnv64)
description:
Literature and the Arts (American Historic Places) 
By Ray Spangenburg and Diane K. Moser
Facts On File | January 1997 | ISBN-10: 081603401X | 176 Pages | scanned PDF | 15.2 mb

This book brings the history of literature and the arts in the United States to life through the study of related historical places. Offering a rich and detailed tour through the homes and studios of important American artists, writers, and musicians. Describes the homes of thirteen American writers and artists, including the farm of painter Charles Willson Peale and the childhood home of novelist Willa Cather.
